    "text": "Erdős Problem #865 remains OPEN. Statement: There exists a constant $C>0$ such that, for all large $N$, if $A\\subseteq \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ has size at least $\\frac{5}{8}N+C$ then there are distinct $a,b,c\\in A$ such that $a+b,a+c,b+c\\in A$. A problem of Erdős and Sós (also earlier considered by Choi, Erdős, and Szemerédi [CES75], but Erdős had forgotten this). Topics: number theory, additive combinatorics. Erdős prize: no. Statement is machine-verified in Lean (formal-conjectures). OEIS: possible.",
